    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Half-round or keel-shaped culminations of an outer wall of a church building in Russian architecture. It may also refer to rounded gable heads in English architecture.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
